answers.body_markdown:
You may use a slice with the `,any` XML tag option to tell the [`encoding/xml`][1] package to put any XML tag into it. This is documented at [`xml.Unmarshal()`][2]:

&gt;     If the XML element contains a sub-element that hasn&#39;t matched any
&gt;        of the above rules and the struct has a field with tag &quot;,any&quot;,
&gt;        unmarshal maps the sub-element to that struct field.

For the `&lt;ifindexXX&gt;` tags use another struct which contains an `XMLName` field of type [`xml.Name`][3] so the actual field name will be available if you need to filter only fields that start with `ifindex`.

Let&#39;s parse the following XML:

    &lt;root&gt;
    	&lt;nic_cnt&gt;2&lt;/nic_cnt&gt;
    	&lt;ifindex1&gt;eno1&lt;/ifindex1&gt;
    	&lt;ifindex2&gt;eno2&lt;/ifindex2&gt;
    &lt;/root&gt;

We can model it with:

    type Root struct {
    	NicCnt  int     `xml:&quot;nic_cnt&quot;`
    	Entries []Entry `xml:&quot;,any&quot;`
    }
    
    type Entry struct {
    	XMLName xml.Name
    	Value   string `xml:&quot;,innerxml&quot;`
    }

Example code parsing it:

	var root Root
	if err := xml.Unmarshal([]byte(src), &amp;root); err != nil {
		panic(err)
	}
	fmt.Printf(&quot;%+v&quot;, root)

Output (try it on the [Go Playground][4]):

    {NicCnt:2 Entries:[
        {XMLName:{Space: Local:ifindex1} Value:eno1}
        {XMLName:{Space: Local:ifindex2} Value:eno2}]}

Note that `Root.Entries` will also contain other unmapped XML tags. If you only care about tags that start with `ifindex`, this is how you can &quot;filter&quot; them:

	for _, e := range root.Entries {
		if strings.HasPrefix(e.XMLName.Local, &quot;ifindex&quot;) {
			fmt.Println(e.XMLName.Local, &quot;:&quot;, e.Value)
		}
	}

If the XML also contains an additional tag:

    &lt;other&gt;something else&lt;/other&gt;

Output will be (try this one on the [Go Playground][5]):

    {NicCnt:2 Entries:[
        {XMLName:{Space: Local:ifindex1} Value:eno1}
        {XMLName:{Space: Local:ifindex2} Value:eno2}
        {XMLName:{Space: Local:other} Value:something else}]}
    ifindex1 : eno1
    ifindex2 : eno2

    


  [1]: https://golang.org/pkg/encoding/xml/
  [2]: https://golang.org/pkg/encoding/xml/#Unmarshal
  [3]: https://golang.org/pkg/encoding/xml/#Name
  [4]: https://play.golang.org/p/noS5n6PgSig
  [5]: https://play.golang.org/p/BNrIiiXl8_R

